{
  "texts": [
    "Trailing GPT-4 Turbo, the other AI agents-GPT-4, Claude 2.1, the new Bard (Gemini 1.0 Pro), Claude 2, GPT-3.5 Turbo, and the legacy Bard (PaLM 2)-ranked successively, surpassing 94%, 90%, 83.3%, 53%, 36.7%, and 12% of human test-takers, respectively.",
    "Echoing the pattern observed in human candidates, all AI agents exhibited stronger results in verbal reasoning over quantitative reasoning.",
    "The extent of this performance gap between the two sections, however, showed variation among the AI agents.",
    "Interestingly, the most recent versions of LLMs, such as the new Bard (Gemini 1.0 Pro), Claude 2.1, and GPT-4 Turbo, closely emulated human test-taker performance patterns.",
    "The discrepancy between their verbal and quantitative scores was nearly identical to the average human candidate's spread."
  ]
}